post_text: This message DOES NOT apply to you if you have enrolled your students in the the 100% Online Virtual School. When the district begins the Hybrid option of attending school, your student(s) will automatically be assigned to groupings, as follows: Last Name begins with A-L – assigned to Group A (Attending school on Monday/Tuesday) Last Name begins with M-Z – assigned to Group B (Attending school on Thursday/Friday) If this process does not allow for siblings to be on the same day, please click on the link below and complete a request for your child to be moved between the groups. We will work to accommodate all requests that are entered, in order to assist your family with scheduling; if you have any questions, please contact the school principal. https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSevhRGS1o08Ig5rlcLnM-HBKT2Rk5xBXM1htmtx1OyuOpvFjg/viewform

post_text:
The Carlsbad High School Spirit Team is ready to kick off its 2020-2021 season! Tryouts and clinics will be held on July 20 & 21 for the CHS Cheer Team and on July 27 & 28 for the CHS Dance Team. Options will also be available for anyone who would like to try out but are unable to attend tryouts on these specific dates. Please visit carlsbadschools.net and go to the Athletics page to find the mandatory survey or click on the link (https://apc01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fforms.gle%2FiDNx4wVL6NP8W2Sm9&data=02%7C01%7C%7Cbb00a3e14f35456c7d2b08d81c7b2951%7C84df9e7fe9f640afb435aaaaaaaaaaaa%7C1%7C0%7C637290662582586928&sdata=d8yJF%2FYlEh3V6nZJrl9IdvLKonXbwsWj6qq1%2BHMahG0%3D&reserved=0) no later than July 13th. You will then receive all of the information on the paperwork needed and more details on the audition process. We are excited to start our year and look forward to seeing all of you!

For more information, please email cheri.young@carlsbadschools.net

post_text:
Congratulations to Tammy Ruiz - One of our Teachers of the Year!
Her colleague, Mirna Rojas, states that Tammy "is always willing to help other teachers with her knowledge. She is willing and always has the disposition to work in collaboration with others. She loves making learning challenging and enjoyable for her students as she is always looking on how to be a better teacher. Tammy is an effective teacher. She always gets the work done. I love that she is a humble, caring, positive and flexible leader to me, her students and all who seek her assistance." Congratulations Tammy!

Congratulations to Suzanne Garza - One of our Teachers of the Year!
Her colleague, Victoria Gonzales, has this to say about Suzanne. "She comes in early and stays late. She strives every single day to teach all her kids the best she can. She stays up with data, strategies and good practices. Suzanne isn’t afraid to speak her mind. Right is right and wrong is wrong. She maintains a clean environment for her students in which she vacuums her own room almost daily. That is devotion on another level. She is one of the hardest working persons I know, and her efforts truly do benefit all of her scholars" Congratulations Suzannne!

post_text:
Congratulations to Patsy Echavarria - Secretary of the Year!

Her principal, Deborah Beard, exclaims that "Patsy has been able to keep me straight for many years. Without her, I would have been lost. She has a wonderful relationship with the scholars, who love her to death. She is great with parents, teachers and anyone who comes into the school. She is professional, very pleasant and as big of a Yankee fan as I am. Her nickname is Mrs. Jeter!" Her assistant principal, Janice Rodriguez, also has this to say about Patsy..."Patsy has been the glue that holds the school together and always does it with a smile!" Hats off to you Patsy!
text:
Congratulations to Patsy Echavarria - Secretary of the Year!

Her principal, Deborah Beard, exclaims that "Patsy has been able to keep me straight for many years. Without her, I would have been lost. She has a wonderful relationship with the scholars, who love her to death. She is great with parents, teachers and anyone who comes into the school. She is professional, very pleasant and as big of a Yankee fan as I am. Her nickname is Mrs. Jeter!" Her assistant principal, Janice Rodriguez, also has this to say about Patsy..."Patsy has been the glue that holds the school together and always does it with a smile!" Hats off to you Patsy!

*As posted on the City of Carlsbad NM Government page...

XTO is inspired by the innovative and creativity Carlsbad Municipal School Administrators and staff are implementing now that living rooms are transformed into classrooms. As a result of their hard work, ExxonMobil Foundation is helping Carlsbad families through the school district with a $100,000 donation. This grant is to help our school district transition from classroom learning to online remote learning. Attached is the press release sent to media outlets in the area and statewide. It will also be promoted on our corporate social media platforms. We've asked the school district to also promote on their respective platforms as they feel necessary. Our teachers need support and encouragement during these difficult times. We hope that our contribution to the Carlsbad Municipal School District will help provide area teachers with the resources they need to continue the important work of educating our next generation of leaders and innovators.
